4
00:00:14,975 --> 00:00:18,396
(Kim Shin Rok, Yoon Je Moon, Cho Han Chul)

5
00:00:18,795 --> 00:00:22,232
(Kim Nam Hee, Park Ji Hyun)

6
00:00:24,613 --> 00:00:27,691
(Jung Hye Young, Kim Young Jae)

7
00:00:31,379 --> 00:00:35,167
(Kim Jung Nan, Kim Do Hyun,
Kim Hyun, Seo Jae Hee)

8
00:00:46,782 --> 00:00:51,081
(Reborn Rich)

9
00:00:51,161 --> 00:00:53,496
(This production is supported by Ministry
of Culture, Sports and Tourism and KOCCA.)

10
00:00:53,850 --> 00:00:55,490
(The characters, institutions,
companies, events, geographical names,)

11
00:00:55,571 --> 00:00:57,340
(and specific countries in this
drama are fictitious.)

12
00:00:58,066 --> 00:00:59,656
Les exportations de la Corée ont augmenté...

13
00:00:59,736 --> 00:01:02,486
de plus de 30 % au premier semestre,

14
00:01:02,566 --> 00:01:04,955
ce qui était le plus élevé parmi
les principaux partenaires commerciaux du pays.

15
00:01:05,035 --> 00:01:06,325
On disait que la Corée...

16
00:01:06,405 --> 00:01:08,896
n'avait jamais été aussi prospère
depuis la fondation de son tout premier royaume.

17
00:01:08,976 --> 00:01:11,095
Les gens croyaient que l'économie
continuerait de croître...

18
00:01:11,175 --> 00:01:13,166
et que tout le monde s'enrichirait.

19
00:01:13,246 --> 00:01:14,935
Le Miracle sur le fleuve Han.

20
00:01:15,015 --> 00:01:17,756
Personne ne doutait
de l'avenir apparemment prometteur du pays.

21
00:01:18,786 --> 00:01:21,375
Le gouvernement a finalement décidé
de demander une aide financière...

22
00:01:21,455 --> 00:01:23,485
au Fonds Monétaire International.

23
00:01:24,196 --> 00:01:26,845
Nous devrions tous nous serrer
la ceinture et économiser.

24
00:01:26,925 --> 00:01:28,885
Nous devrions unir nos forces...

25
00:01:28,965 --> 00:01:30,885
et surmonter cette crise ensemble
en cette période difficile.

26
00:01:30,965 --> 00:01:33,155
En admettant que le pays
est pratiquement en faillite,

27
00:01:33,235 --> 00:01:35,026
- le FMI...
- Le pays est en faillite ?

28
00:01:35,106 --> 00:01:37,155
Jusqu'à ce jour.

29
00:01:37,235 --> 00:01:38,836
Zut alors !

30
00:01:40,875 --> 00:01:42,765
Qui aurait cru...

31
00:01:42,845 --> 00:01:45,265
qu'un pays puisse faire faillite ?
C'est inouï !

32
00:01:45,345 --> 00:01:48,685
Le monde que personne n'avait jamais connu
ni imaginé auparavant.

33
00:01:49,646 --> 00:01:52,575
En échange
de l'aide de 21 milliards de dollars,

34
00:01:52,655 --> 00:01:53,776
le FMI demande à la Corée de mettre en œuvre
une ouverture complète du marché,

35
00:01:53,856 --> 00:01:55,545
de promouvoir la flexibilité du marché du travail,

36
00:01:55,625 --> 00:01:58,446
- et de réformer les conglomérats...
- Ces scélérats !

37
00:01:58,526 --> 00:02:00,176
Nous prennent-ils pour leur colonie ?

38
00:02:00,996 --> 00:02:02,265
Leur colonie économique.

39
00:02:03,125 --> 00:02:05,685
Ils pensent qu'ils peuvent nous dépouiller...

40
00:02:05,765 --> 00:02:08,806
parce qu'ils nous donnent quelques dollars.

41
00:02:17,416 --> 00:02:18,476
Alors ?

42
00:02:21,115 --> 00:02:23,485
Comment pouvons-nous survivre ?

43
00:02:26,455 --> 00:02:29,455
Personne d'autre dans le pays n'avait prédit
cette crise nationale...

44
00:02:33,525 --> 00:02:35,125
et ne s'y était préparé...

45
00:02:36,365 --> 00:02:37,395
sauf moi.

46
00:02:54,085 --> 00:02:55,136
Veuillez signer ceci.

47
00:02:55,216 --> 00:02:59,416
Cet accord stipule que Mason Oh
est le PDG de Miracle Investment.

48
00:03:04,696 --> 00:03:06,756
Je voulais vous demander quelque chose.

49
00:03:07,626 --> 00:03:10,576
La crise des changes.
Vous étiez au courant, n'est-ce pas ?

50
00:03:12,536 --> 00:03:16,456
Vous avez échangé 24 millions de dollars
en dollars américains, ce qui est beaucoup d'argent.

51
00:03:16,536 --> 00:03:18,125
Vous êtes venu jusqu'à New York
pour me rencontrer...

52
00:03:18,205 --> 00:03:20,695
et avez fait un investissement
si risqué...

53
00:03:20,775 --> 00:03:23,376
pour gagner des dollars américains
en prévision de ce jour.

54
00:03:23,976 --> 00:03:24,976
N'est-ce pas ?

55
00:03:26,275 --> 00:03:28,736
Même Cheongwadae, les fonctionnaires
financiers,

56
00:03:28,816 --> 00:03:32,015
et les experts ne l'avaient
pas vu venir. Personne ne s'y attendait.

57
00:03:32,786 --> 00:03:35,176
Mais vous, un étudiant
en début de vingtaine,

58
00:03:35,256 --> 00:03:37,356
vous l'aviez vu venir.

59
00:03:40,425 --> 00:03:41,675
Ne trouvez-vous pas ça étrange ?

60
00:03:42,696 --> 00:03:44,365
Votre question était mauvaise, Monsieur Oh.

61
00:03:47,335 --> 00:03:48,785
L'année dernière,
les réserves de change de la Corée...

62
00:03:48,865 --> 00:03:50,655
s'élevaient à 30 milliards de dollars,

63
00:03:50,735 --> 00:03:54,495
tandis que ses passifs se chiffraient
à 170 milliards de dollars,

64
00:03:54,575 --> 00:03:57,866
ce qui signifie que la note
de crédit du pays baissait.

65
00:03:57,946 --> 00:04:01,296
Le montant total des salaires impayés
a dépassé 700 millions de dollars.

66
00:04:04,055 --> 00:04:07,355
Même un jeune étudiant
aurait pu voir qu'une crise était imminente.

67
00:04:08,186 --> 00:04:11,636
Alors pourquoi ceux de Cheongwadae
et les fonctionnaires financiers n'ont-ils pas pu ?

68
00:04:13,455 --> 00:04:14,795
Ne trouvez-vous pas ça étrange ?

69
00:04:16,466 --> 00:04:17,495
Non ?

70
00:04:19,966 --> 00:04:20,966
Bon point.

71
00:04:24,336 --> 00:04:26,026
Grâce à votre clairvoyance,

72
00:04:26,106 --> 00:04:29,805
vous êtes maintenant l'une des rares personnes
qui détiennent le plus de dollars américains en Corée.

73
00:04:30,576 --> 00:04:31,576
Félicitations.

74
00:04:33,476 --> 00:04:36,105
Tout cela fait partie
des actifs de Miracle Investment.

75
00:04:36,185 --> 00:04:38,006
(Jin Do Jun)

76
00:04:38,086 --> 00:04:40,086
"HW ?"

77
00:04:40,685 --> 00:04:43,035
Ce ne sont pas vos initiales.
Qu'est-ce que cela signifie ?

78
00:04:54,565 --> 00:04:55,666
"HW ?"

79
00:04:57,836 --> 00:05:00,505
On vous lit plus facilement que je ne le pensais.

80
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:04,175
Je sais ce que cela signifie.
Howard Hughes. N'est-ce pas ?

81
00:05:04,745 --> 00:05:07,566
HW comme Howard.

82
00:05:07,646 --> 00:05:09,016
Il doit être votre modèle.

83
00:05:09,586 --> 00:05:14,076
N'est-ce pas ? Parce que vous êtes né
héritier d'un millionnaire, tout comme lui ?

84
00:05:14,156 --> 00:05:17,516
Ou parce qu'il a utilisé
avec style son argent et son pouvoir...

85
00:05:17,596 --> 00:05:21,045
pour mettre la main sur tout ce qu'il voulait,
toute sa vie ?

86
00:05:21,125 --> 00:05:23,956
Eh bien, je dirais les deux.

87
00:05:24,036 --> 00:05:25,456
Très bien, Howard.

88
00:05:25,536 --> 00:05:29,065
Quelle est la première entreprise
que Miracle Investment va acquérir ?

89
00:05:33,305 --> 00:05:37,095
Ils pensent qu'elle pourrait
être reprise dans un avenir proche.

90
00:05:37,175 --> 00:05:40,235
Ahjin Motors,
le deuxième plus grand constructeur automobile de Corée,

91
00:05:40,315 --> 00:05:43,266
a déposé une demande de receivership.

92
00:05:43,346 --> 00:05:47,105
Incapable de rembourser le prêt
de 4,5 milliards de dollars,

93
00:05:47,185 --> 00:05:48,535
l'entreprise a finalement coulé...

94
00:05:50,425 --> 00:05:51,946
Vous voulez acheter Ahjin Motors ?

95
00:05:52,026 --> 00:05:53,596
Avec toutes les dettes ?

96
00:05:54,365 --> 00:05:56,625
Attendez. Non, n'est-ce pas ?

97
00:05:57,966 --> 00:06:02,135
Vous avez dit que vous visiez
quelque chose de plus gros que Soonyang.

98
00:06:02,766 --> 00:06:04,466
Ne me dites pas que c'était Ahjin Motors.

99
00:06:05,635 --> 00:06:07,745
Pourquoi ? Pourquoi Ahjin ?

100
00:06:09,545 --> 00:06:11,045
Cela convient à notre entreprise.

101
00:06:12,445 --> 00:06:13,476
Miracle.

102
00:06:14,245 --> 00:06:15,245
Regardez.

103
00:06:17,086 --> 00:06:18,086
Un miracle ?

104
00:06:18,985 --> 00:06:20,726
Ahjin ? Ahjin Motors, sérieusement ?

105
00:06:27,396 --> 00:06:29,666
(Ahjin Motors)

106
00:06:33,036 --> 00:06:34,126
(Ahjin Motors)

107
00:06:34,206 --> 00:06:35,956
- Mon Dieu.
- Allons-y.

108
00:06:36,036 --> 00:06:38,326
- Nous avons fait de notre mieux.
- Allons-y.

109
00:06:38,406 --> 00:06:39,756
- Allez.
- Allons-y.

110
00:06:39,836 --> 00:06:42,126
- Maudit soit-il !
- Sales pourritures !

111
00:06:42,206 --> 00:06:43,365
- Allons-y.
- Que devrions-nous faire maintenant ?

112
00:06:43,445 --> 00:06:44,865
Comment vais-je gagner ma vie ?

113
00:06:44,945 --> 00:06:46,276
- Zut alors.
- Mon Dieu.

114
00:06:47,045 --> 00:06:49,845
- Que faisons-nous maintenant ?
- Sérieusement, qu'est-ce que je vais faire ?

115
00:06:51,516 --> 00:06:52,656
Zut alors !

116
00:06:53,286 --> 00:06:54,956
- Mon Dieu.
- Je n'arrive pas à croire cela.

117
00:06:55,856 --> 00:06:59,915
(Reborn Rich)

118
00:06:59,995 --> 00:07:00,946
(Vaincre la crise nationale,
Ouvrir une nouvelle ère)

119
00:07:01,026 --> 00:07:04,795
(Février 1998)

120
00:07:08,065 --> 00:07:11,235
Cette année, les prix continueront d'augmenter,

121
00:07:11,805 --> 00:07:13,655
et de plus en plus de personnes perdront leur emploi.

122
00:07:14,175 --> 00:07:17,795
Les revenus de chacun diminueront,
et de plus en plus d'entreprises feront faillite.

123
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:21,445
Nous devrons tous verser
beaucoup de sueur et de larmes...

124
00:07:24,786 --> 00:07:26,856
en traversant cette période difficile.

125
00:07:29,526 --> 00:07:31,816
Il est enfin devenu Président
après trois tentatives ratées. Mais pour quoi faire ?

126
00:07:31,896 --> 00:07:34,785
On lui a remis la clé d'un hangar vide.

127
00:07:34,865 --> 00:07:37,115
Mon Dieu. Quelle malchance.

128
00:07:37,195 --> 00:07:38,256
Il voudra qu'on se souvienne de lui...

129
00:07:38,336 --> 00:07:41,666
comme du président qui a rempli le hangar
et donné une leçon aux riches.

130
00:07:42,406 --> 00:07:44,355
Ils appellent ça une réunion pour le petit-déjeuner.

131
00:07:44,435 --> 00:07:46,655
Mais clairement, ils nous ont convoqués
tous pour nous discipliner.

132
00:07:46,735 --> 00:07:48,496
À cette heure matinale...

133
00:07:48,576 --> 00:07:51,315
Bref, dormez-vous bien ces temps-ci ?

134
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:53,965
Vous savez, la situation d'Ahjin Motors.

135
00:07:54,045 --> 00:07:55,845
Cela pourrait nous arriver aussi, vous savez.

136
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:01,946
Même Ahjin, la deuxième plus grande
entreprise automobile, s'est effondrée.

137
00:08:02,026 --> 00:08:04,396
Soonyang Motors sera-t-elle épargnée ?

138
00:08:05,925 --> 00:08:09,345
Après vous avoir écouté,
je suis effectivement préoccupé.

139
00:08:09,425 --> 00:08:10,446
(Cheongwadae, La République de Corée)

140
00:08:10,526 --> 00:08:13,155
Daeyoung Motors
est le numéro un des constructeurs automobiles.

141
00:08:13,235 --> 00:08:17,026
L'entreprise devrait se mondialiser
et rapporter des dollars, si quoi que ce soit.

142
00:08:17,106 --> 00:08:20,336
Mais ils sont occupés à faire du pouvoir
dans ce petit pays.

143
00:08:22,906 --> 00:08:25,416
Se mondialiser sera difficile, n'est-ce pas ?

144
00:08:26,846 --> 00:08:28,985
Soonyang devrait-il vous montrer comment faire ?

145
00:08:36,985 --> 00:08:39,935
Président Jin, vous êtes sûrement bien
plus magnanime que moi.

146
00:08:41,726 --> 00:08:43,265
Votre fils cadet.

147
00:08:45,495 --> 00:08:48,726
Il est venu me voir et m'a dit qu'il voulait
reprendre Hando Steel.

148
00:08:48,806 --> 00:08:50,685
S'il avait été mon fils,

149
00:08:50,765 --> 00:08:53,706
je lui aurais donné une leçon
et l'aurais déshérité il y a longtemps.

150
00:08:54,676 --> 00:08:57,966
Ce gamin a osé poignarder
son frère dans le dos.

151
00:08:58,046 --> 00:09:00,275
Mais vous l'avez protégé
parce que c'est votre fils.

152
00:09:03,285 --> 00:09:04,285
Cela a certainement...

153
00:09:05,456 --> 00:09:06,785
changé mon opinion sur vous.

154
00:09:08,956 --> 00:09:11,696
- Vous...
- Monsieur le Président est là.

155
00:09:19,336 --> 00:09:21,126
Que pense Cheongwadae ?

156
00:09:21,206 --> 00:09:23,726
Ils n'ont même pas évoqué
le FMI et la succession d'entreprises, n'est-ce pas ?

157
00:09:23,806 --> 00:09:25,856
Vont-ils réformer le système des conglomérats ?

158
00:09:26,735 --> 00:09:29,046
Veulent-ils que nous perdions
toutes nos filiales ?

159
00:09:29,576 --> 00:09:32,466
Oh, bien sûr. J'ai entendu dire
que nous devrons peut-être céder
nos actifs privés aussi.

160
00:09:32,546 --> 00:09:33,816
Cela n'arrivera pas, n'est-ce pas ?

161
00:09:35,145 --> 00:09:36,945
Avez-vous déjà
accepté tout cela ?

162
00:09:37,556 --> 00:09:39,385
- Père.
- Dong Ki !

163
00:09:41,326 --> 00:09:42,426
Toi...

164
00:09:55,206 --> 00:09:57,235
Cheongwadae semblait déterminé.

165
00:09:57,875 --> 00:10:00,455
Ils prévoient de restructurer
les grandes entreprises,

166
00:10:00,535 --> 00:10:02,285
et Soonyang
ne fera pas exception.

167
00:10:09,245 --> 00:10:12,255
Que fera Cheongwadae
concernant Ahjin Motors ?

168
00:10:14,426 --> 00:10:17,545
S'ils tardent à régler la question,
l'entreprise accumulera plus de dettes.

169
00:10:17,625 --> 00:10:19,246
Alors personne ne voudra
acquérir l'entreprise.

170
00:10:19,326 --> 00:10:21,886
L'industrie automobile nationale
souffre énormément.

171
00:10:21,966 --> 00:10:23,685
Qui serait prêt à acquérir Ahjin Motors ?

172
00:10:23,765 --> 00:10:26,716
Qui serait assez fou pour faire ça,
à moins d'avoir reçu une balle dans la tête ?

173
00:10:26,796 --> 00:10:27,806
Moi.

174
00:10:30,165 --> 00:10:31,635
Ahjin Motors.

175
00:10:32,706 --> 00:10:34,446
Soonyang achètera l'entreprise.

176
00:10:35,405 --> 00:10:38,636
Père, vous souhaitez acheter Ahjin
avec tout ce qui se passe ?

177
00:10:38,716 --> 00:10:41,435
Si un homme d'affaires reste
dans une zone de sécurité et ne bouge pas,

178
00:10:41,515 --> 00:10:42,636
son derrière va pourrir.

179
00:10:42,716 --> 00:10:46,356
Père, les intérêts sur leur prêt
sont de 30 %.

180
00:10:47,015 --> 00:10:48,506
Ahjin n'a rien que des dettes.

181
00:10:48,586 --> 00:10:50,445
Voulez-vous vous porter volontaire
pour vous occuper de la bombe ?

182
00:10:50,525 --> 00:10:53,116
Pour le moment, nous devrions nous concentrer
sur le maintien de Soonyang Motors...

183
00:10:53,196 --> 00:10:55,446
Cheongwadae souhaite
tout restructurer.

184
00:10:57,196 --> 00:11:00,346
Et comme vous l'avez dit,
l'industrie automobile nationale est morte.

185
00:11:03,365 --> 00:11:06,576
Pourquoi ne comprenez-vous pas ce que cela signifie ?

186
00:11:07,235 --> 00:11:09,165
Ahjin Motors n'est pas la bombe.

187
00:11:09,245 --> 00:11:11,065
Soonyang Motors l'est.

188
00:11:11,145 --> 00:11:14,295
Le constructeur automobile le moins performant
du pays, Soonyang Motors !

189
00:11:19,816 --> 00:11:21,485
Acquérir Ahjin Motors ?

190
00:11:22,525 --> 00:11:23,826
Ce n'est pas un choix.

191
00:11:24,596 --> 00:11:25,846
Nous devons le faire pour survivre.

192
00:11:27,765 --> 00:11:28,796
Pour survivre.

193
00:11:30,265 --> 00:11:31,336
D'accord ?

194
00:11:32,495 --> 00:11:33,596
Comprenez-vous ?

195
00:11:37,806 --> 00:11:41,505
(Ahjin Motors, Changements d'actionnaires)

196
00:11:47,546 --> 00:11:50,015
Votre grand-père, le Président Jin.

197
00:11:51,015 --> 00:11:54,216
Il sera déterminé
à acquérir Ahjin Motors.

198
00:11:55,086 --> 00:11:58,116
Parce que c'est la seule façon
de protéger Soonyang Motors.

199
00:11:58,196 --> 00:12:00,646
Acquérir Ahjin Motors,
la numéro deux de l'industrie,

200
00:12:00,726 --> 00:12:02,445
signifie que leur part de marché augmentera.

201
00:12:02,525 --> 00:12:04,455
Et s'ils partagent les chaînes de production,

202
00:12:04,535 --> 00:12:06,785
ils peuvent aussi réduire les coûts.

203
00:12:06,865 --> 00:12:09,905
Plus important encore,
ils devraient faire croître Soonyang Motors...

204
00:12:11,005 --> 00:12:12,195
pour éviter la restructuration.

205
00:12:12,275 --> 00:12:13,306
(Soonyang)

206
00:12:17,206 --> 00:12:18,716
Cela dit...

207
00:12:22,586 --> 00:12:26,186
Si j'étais l'une de ces personnes
à Cheongwadae,

208
00:12:27,586 --> 00:12:29,486
je donnerais Ahjin Motors au Président Jin.

209
00:12:30,456 --> 00:12:32,246
Pas à une nouvelle société d'investissement comme nous...

210
00:12:32,326 --> 00:12:34,526
sans aucune expérience
en gestion.

211
00:12:35,765 --> 00:12:37,085
Êtes-vous confiant ?

212
00:12:37,165 --> 00:12:39,655
Êtes-vous sûr que nous ne perdrons pas
Ahjin Motors au profit de Soonyang ?

213
00:12:39,735 --> 00:12:42,685
Je vous assure que Soonyang
n'acquérira jamais Ahjin Motors.

214
00:12:46,576 --> 00:12:48,976
Ils réaliseront bientôt qu'ils sont tombés
victimes...

215
00:12:50,346 --> 00:12:51,676
de la malédiction du vainqueur.

216
00:12:54,745 --> 00:12:56,546
Les réserves internes ?

217
00:12:57,785 --> 00:13:00,056
- Tout ?
- Oui.

218
00:13:00,716 --> 00:13:02,945
La guerre d'enchères concernant Hando Steel...

219
00:13:03,025 --> 00:13:05,655
a été extrêmement féroce, père.

220
00:13:06,726 --> 00:13:09,646
Avec les différences de change
qui s'envolaient,

221
00:13:09,726 --> 00:13:11,365
nous avons eu des dépenses imprévues, monsieur.

222
00:13:15,106 --> 00:13:16,206
Que pouvons-nous faire ?

223
00:13:17,635 --> 00:13:19,385
Essayez d'obtenir un prêt auprès d'une banque.

224
00:13:20,706 --> 00:13:23,565
Nous avons atteint nos limites
dans toutes les grandes banques,

225
00:13:23,645 --> 00:13:25,895
donc nous ne pouvons pas obtenir
un prêt supplémentaire, monsieur.

226
00:13:30,686 --> 00:13:32,486
Est-ce aussi à cause de Hando Steel ?

227
00:13:33,985 --> 00:13:35,025
Oui, monsieur.

228
00:13:42,265 --> 00:13:43,615
Nos biens immobiliers.

229
00:13:44,796 --> 00:13:46,066
Vendons-les.

230
00:13:47,265 --> 00:13:48,265
Le problème, c'est que,

231
00:13:49,436 --> 00:13:51,236
nous avons déjà utilisé les plus précieux...

232
00:13:51,806 --> 00:13:53,706
- comme garantie pour obtenir...
- Alors ?

233
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:57,816
Dites-vous que nous n'avons pas les moyens
d'acquérir Ahjin Motors ?

234
00:13:59,716 --> 00:14:00,946
Je suis désolé, père.

235
00:14:06,216 --> 00:14:09,376
Nous n'aurions eu aucun problème
sans la crise financière.

236
00:14:09,456 --> 00:14:11,945
Si seulement Dong Ki n'avait pas incité
le président de Daeyoung...

237
00:14:12,025 --> 00:14:14,246
à augmenter l'offre pour Hando Steel...

238
00:14:14,326 --> 00:14:16,216
Père, j'étais juste...

239
00:14:16,296 --> 00:14:17,495
Assez, vous deux !

240
00:14:22,365 --> 00:14:25,005
C'est entièrement de ma faute.

241
00:14:26,336 --> 00:14:27,405
Père.

242
00:14:30,846 --> 00:14:31,946
Hang Jae.

243
00:14:38,255 --> 00:14:39,316
Oui, monsieur.

244
00:14:40,985 --> 00:14:42,086
Tu es...

245
00:14:44,525 --> 00:14:46,326
mon fils.

246
00:14:53,495 --> 00:14:55,265
(Arrivées Sortie)

247
00:15:14,985 --> 00:15:16,155
Monsieur Jin Seong Jun ?

248
00:15:20,655 --> 00:15:22,705
Vous attendez votre secrétaire, n'est-ce pas ?

249
00:15:24,466 --> 00:15:25,995
Ils seront un peu en retard.

250
00:15:27,566 --> 00:15:30,566
Oui, désolé ! Oh, mon Dieu.

251
00:15:31,535 --> 00:15:33,795
Désolés. Nous nous excusons.

252
00:15:33,875 --> 00:15:35,446
- Nous sommes désolés.
- Mon Dieu.

253
00:15:36,106 --> 00:15:37,496
Vous les gars.

254
00:15:37,576 --> 00:15:40,535
- Vous ne pouvez pas bloquer la route !
- Nous sommes désolés.

255
00:15:40,615 --> 00:15:42,606
- Désolé, nous allons nous dépêcher.
- Je suis très occupé en ce moment !

256
00:15:42,686 --> 00:15:45,456
Ils sont bloqués.

257
00:15:47,885 --> 00:15:50,506
Nos valises ont été échangées à l'aéroport,

258
00:15:50,586 --> 00:15:52,516
donc nous nous rencontrons par destin...

259
00:15:52,596 --> 00:15:55,486
et laissons une profonde impression
les uns sur les autres. C'est l'histoire.

260
00:15:55,566 --> 00:15:57,696
Avant que nos familles ne nous marient officiellement.

261
00:15:58,635 --> 00:16:00,415
- "Nous ?"
- Jin Seong Jun,

262
00:16:00,495 --> 00:16:01,825
l'aîné des petits-fils
de la famille Soonyang,

263
00:16:01,905 --> 00:16:05,496
et Mo Hyeon Min, la seule fille
de la famille Hyunsung Daily.

264
00:16:05,576 --> 00:16:06,576
Nous.

265
00:16:07,905 --> 00:16:09,866
En entendant dire que vous seriez rebuté
par les négociations de mariage...

266
00:16:09,946 --> 00:16:12,266
entre les deux familles,

267
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:14,266
ma famille a eu cette idée
en urgence...

268
00:16:14,346 --> 00:16:17,435
parce qu'ils veulent vraiment
me marier à votre famille.

269
00:16:17,515 --> 00:16:21,015
Vous me montrez toutes vos cartes.
Alors ce jeu ne sera pas amusant.

270
00:16:23,785 --> 00:16:25,276
En troisième année d'université, vous avez suivi...

271
00:16:25,356 --> 00:16:28,726
"Comprendre la littérature classique britannique
et américaine". C moins.

272
00:16:29,395 --> 01:07:53,586
C'était votre note, n'est-ce pas ?

273
00:16:31,765 --> 00:16:34,285
Pas étonnant que vous ayez
de faibles compétences en compréhension.

274
00:16:34,365 --> 00:16:37,065
J'essaie de vous dire
qu'il faut renverser la vapeur.

275
00:16:43,745 --> 00:16:47,245
Vous avez l'air de penser :
"D'où sort ce cinglé ?"

276
00:16:48,816 --> 00:16:50,566
Vous avez une bonne compréhension.

277
00:16:51,356 --> 00:16:53,575
Oui, vous voyez.

278
00:16:53,655 --> 00:16:55,885
Dites aux aînés de votre famille.

279
00:16:56,785 --> 00:16:59,815
Je m'aime trop pour parier mon avenir
sur vous simplement parce que...

280
00:16:59,895 --> 00:17:01,685
vous êtes de la famille Soonyang.

281
00:17:01,765 --> 00:17:03,646
Pourquoi ne vous en occupez-vous
pas vous-même ?

282
00:17:03,726 --> 00:17:06,836
Ma famille n'est pas vraiment
en position de refuser.

283
00:17:16,746 --> 00:17:19,746
Vous êtes plus beau en personne.
Je suppose que vous n'êtes pas photogénique.

284
00:17:41,836 --> 00:17:44,036
Je suis désolé, monsieur.
Vous ai-je fait attendre longtemps ?

285
00:17:45,006 --> 00:17:46,496
Vous ne me croierez peut-être pas,

286
00:17:46,576 --> 00:17:48,565
mais un camion de livraison
de journal stupide...

287
00:17:48,645 --> 00:17:51,436
Bien sûr, je vous crois.
C'était Hyunsung Daily, n'est-ce pas ?

288
00:17:51,516 --> 00:17:53,166
Oh, comment le saviez-vous ?

289
00:17:53,246 --> 00:17:55,215
Allons-y. Les aînés doivent attendre.

290
00:17:56,016 --> 00:17:57,046
Oui, monsieur.

291
00:18:01,986 --> 00:18:04,856
- Grand-mère.
- Oh, mon Dieu.

292
00:18:05,526 --> 00:18:08,746
Mon Dieu. Tu as réussi, mon chéri.

293
00:18:08,826 --> 00:18:10,566
Ça a dû être si dur.

294
00:18:11,365 --> 00:18:14,926
Vous avez vécu de hamburgers
en étudiant dans ce pays lointain.

295
00:18:15,006 --> 00:18:17,125
Vous avez maigri.

296
00:18:17,205 --> 00:18:19,496
Non. J'ai pris 5 kg, grand-mère.

297
00:18:19,576 --> 00:18:20,956
C'est de la rétention d'eau.

298
00:18:21,036 --> 00:18:23,196
Vous êtes gonflée parce que
vous n'avez pas bien mangé.

299
00:18:23,276 --> 00:18:26,135
Jeong Rae, qu'attendez-vous ? Il doit avoir faim.

300
00:18:26,215 --> 00:18:28,436
- Nourrissons-le d'abord.
- D'accord.

301
00:18:28,516 --> 00:18:31,286
- Mère, il devrait d'abord dire bonjour
à son père.
- D'accord.

302
00:18:31,856 --> 00:18:34,746
- D'accord.
- Il est dans son bureau, n'est-ce pas ?

303
00:00:01,188 --> 00:00:03,790
(Song Joong Ki)

304
00:00:05,431 --> 00:00:08,001
(Lee Sung Min)

305
00:00:11,553 --> 00:00:14,638
(Shin Hyun Been)

306
00:00:14,975 --> 00:00:18,396
(Kim Shin Rok, Yoon Je Moon, Cho Han Chul)

307
00:00:18,795 --> 00:00:22,232
(Kim Nam Hee, Park Ji Hyun)

308
00:00:24,613 --> 00:00:27,691
(Jung Hye Young, Kim Young Jae)

309
00:00:31,379 --> 00:00:35,167
(Kim Jung Nan, Kim Do Hyun,
Kim Hyun, Seo Jae Hee)

310
00:00:46,782 --> 00:00:51,081
(Reborn Rich)

311
00:00:51,161 --> 00:00:53,496
(This production is supported by Ministry
of Culture, Sports and Tourism and KOCCA.)

312
00:00:53,850 --> 00:00:55,490
(The characters, institutions,
companies, events, geographical names,)

313
00:00:55,571 --> 00:00:57,340
(and specific countries in this
drama are fictitious.)

314
00:00:58,066 --> 00:00:59,656
Korea's exports went up...

315
00:00:59,736 --> 00:01:02,486
by over 30 percent
in the 1st half of the year,

316
00:01:02,566 --> 00:01:04,955
which was the highest among
the nation's major trading partners.

317
00:01:05,035 --> 00:01:06,325
People said Korea...

318
00:01:06,405 --> 00:01:08,896
had never been so prosperous
since its very first kingdom was founded.

319
00:01:08,976 --> 00:01:11,095
People believed that the economy
would continue to grow...

320
00:01:11,175 --> 00:01:13,166
and that everyone would become richer.

321
00:01:13,246 --> 00:01:14,935
The Miracle on the Han River.

322
00:01:15,015 --> 00:01:17,756
No one doubted
the nation's seemingly rosy future.

323
00:01:18,786 --> 00:01:21,375
The government has finally decided
to seek financial assistance...

324
00:01:21,455 --> 00:01:23,485
from the International Monetary Fund.

325
00:01:24,196 --> 00:01:26,845
We should all scrimp and save.

326
00:01:26,925 --> 00:01:28,885
We should join forces...

327
00:01:28,965 --> 00:01:30,885
and overcome this crisis together
at this difficult time.

328
00:01:30,965 --> 00:01:33,155
Upon admitting that the country
is basically bankrupt,

329
00:01:33,235 --> 00:01:35,026
- the IMF...
- The country is bankrupt?

330
00:01:35,106 --> 00:01:37,155
Until that day came.

331
00:01:37,235 --> 00:01:38,836
Darn it!

332
00:01:40,875 --> 00:01:42,765
Who knew...

333
00:01:42,845 --> 00:01:45,265
a country could go bankrupt?
This is unheard of!

334
00:01:45,345 --> 00:01:48,685
The world no one had ever experienced
or imagined before.

335
00:01:49,646 --> 00:01:52,575
In return for
the 21 billion-dollar aid package,

336
00:01:52,655 --> 00:01:53,776
the IMF is requesting that Korea implement
complete market opening,

337
00:01:53,856 --> 00:01:55,545
promote labor market flexibility,

338
00:01:55,625 --> 00:01:58,446
- and reform the conglomerates...
- Those scoundrels!

339
00:01:58,526 --> 00:02:00,176
Do they think we're their colony?

340
00:02:00,996 --> 00:02:02,265
Their economic colony.

341
00:02:03,125 --> 00:02:05,685
They think they can strip us bare...

342
00:02:05,765 --> 00:02:08,806
because they're giving us a few dollars.

343
00:02:17,416 --> 00:02:18,476
So?

344
00:02:21,115 --> 00:02:23,485
What can we do to survive?

345
00:02:26,455 --> 00:02:29,455
No one else in the country predicted
this national crisis...

346
00:02:33,525 --> 00:02:35,125
and has been preparing for it...

347
00:02:36,365 --> 00:02:37,395
except for me.

348
00:02:54,085 --> 00:02:55,136
Please sign this.

349
00:02:55,216 --> 00:02:59,416
This agreement states that Mason Oh
is the CEO of Miracle Investment.

350
00:03:04,696 --> 00:03:06,756
I wanted to ask you something.

351
00:03:07,626 --> 00:03:10,576
The foreign exchange crisis.
You knew about it, didn't you?

352
00:03:12,536 --> 00:03:16,456
You exchanged 24 million dollars
to US dollars, which is a lot of money.

353
00:03:16,536 --> 00:03:18,125
You came all the way
to New York to meet me...

354
00:03:18,205 --> 00:03:20,695
and made such a risky investment...

355
00:03:20,775 --> 00:03:23,376
to earn US dollars
in preparation for this day.

356
00:03:23,976 --> 00:03:24,976
Right?

357
00:03:26,275 --> 00:03:28,736
Even Cheongwadae, financial officers,

358
00:03:28,816 --> 00:03:32,015
and experts didn't see this coming.
No one expected this.

359
00:03:32,786 --> 00:03:35,176
But you, a college student
in his early 20s,

360
00:03:35,256 --> 00:03:37,356
saw it coming.

361
00:03:40,425 --> 00:03:41,675
Don't you think it's odd?

362
00:03:42,696 --> 00:03:44,365
Your question was wrong, Mr. Oh.

363
00:03:47,335 --> 00:03:48,785
Last year,
Korea's foreign exchange reserves...

364
00:03:48,865 --> 00:03:50,655
stood at 30 billion dollars,

365
00:03:50,735 --> 00:03:54,495
whereas its liabilities were
measured at 170 billion dollars,

366
00:03:54,575 --> 00:03:57,866
which means that the country's
credit rating has been dropping.

367
00:03:57,946 --> 00:04:01,296
The total amount of unpaid wages
has surpassed 700 million dollars.

368
00:04:04,055 --> 00:04:07,355
Even a young college student could see
that a crisis was imminent.

369
00:04:08,186 --> 00:04:11,636
So how come those at Cheongwadae
and the financial officers couldn't?

370
00:04:13,455 --> 00:04:14,795
Don't you think it's odd?

371
00:04:16,466 --> 00:04:17,495
No?

372
00:04:19,966 --> 00:04:20,966
Good point.

373
00:04:24,336 --> 00:04:26,026
Thanks to your foresight,

374
00:04:26,106 --> 00:04:29,805
you're now one of the people
who hold the most US dollars in Korea.

375
00:04:30,576 --> 00:04:31,576
Congratulations.

376
00:04:33,476 --> 00:04:36,105
It's all part of
Miracle Investment's assets.

377
00:04:36,185 --> 00:04:38,006
(Jin Do Jun)

378
00:04:38,086 --> 00:04:40,086
"HW?"

379
00:04:40,685 --> 00:04:43,035
They're not your initials.
What does that mean?

380
00:04:54,565 --> 00:04:55,666
"HW?"

381
00:04:57,836 --> 00:05:00,505
You're easier to read than I thought.

382
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:04,175
I know what it stands for.
Howard Hughes. Right?

383
00:05:04,745 --> 00:05:07,566
HW as in Howard.

384
00:05:07,646 --> 00:05:09,016
He must be your role model.

385
00:05:09,586 --> 00:05:14,076
Right. Because you were born as
a millionaire's heir, just like him?

386
00:05:14,156 --> 00:05:17,516
Or because he fashionably used
his money and power...

387
00:05:17,596 --> 00:05:21,045
to get his hands on everything he wanted,
all his life?

388
00:05:21,125 --> 00:05:23,956
Well, I'd say it's both.

389
00:05:24,036 --> 00:05:25,456
All right, Howard.

390
00:05:25,536 --> 00:05:29,065
What's the first company Miracle Investment
will acquire?

391
00:05:33,305 --> 00:05:37,095
They believe it could be resumed
in the near future.

392
00:05:37,175 --> 00:05:40,235
Ahjin Motors,
Korea's second biggest automaker,

393
00:05:40,315 --> 00:05:43,266
has filed for court receivership.

394
00:05:43,346 --> 00:05:47,105
Unable to repay the loan
of 4.5 billion dollars,

395
00:05:47,185 --> 00:05:48,535
the company finally sank...

396
00:05:50,425 --> 00:05:51,946
You want to buy Ahjin Motors?

397
00:05:52,026 --> 00:05:53,596
With all the debts?

398
00:05:54,365 --> 00:05:56,625
Hold on. No, right?

399
00:05:57,966 --> 00:06:02,135
You said you were after something bigger
than Soonyang.

400
00:06:02,766 --> 00:06:04,466
Don't tell me it was Ahjin Motors.

401
00:06:05,635 --> 00:06:07,745
Why? Why Ahjin?

402
00:06:09,545 --> 00:06:11,045
It suits our company.

403
00:06:12,445 --> 00:06:13,476
Miracle.

404
00:06:14,245 --> 00:06:15,245
Look.

405
00:06:17,086 --> 00:06:18,086
A miracle?

406
00:06:18,985 --> 00:06:20,726
Ahjin? Ahjin Motors, seriously?

407
00:06:27,396 --> 00:06:29,666
(Ahjin Motors)

408
00:06:33,036 --> 00:06:34,126
(Ahjin Motors)

409
00:06:34,206 --> 00:06:35,956
- Goodness.
- Let's go.

410
00:06:36,036 --> 00:06:38,326
- We did our best.
- Let's get going.

411
00:06:38,406 --> 00:06:39,756
- Come on.
- Let's go.

412
00:06:39,836 --> 00:06:42,126
- Curse you!
- You scumbags!

413
00:06:42,206 --> 00:06:43,365
- Let's go.
- What should we do now?

414
00:06:43,445 --> 00:06:44,865
How am I going to earn a living?

415
00:06:44,945 --> 00:06:46,276
- Darn it.
- Gosh.

416
00:06:47,045 --> 00:06:49,845
- What do we do now?
- Seriously, what am I going to do?

417
00:06:51,516 --> 00:06:52,656
Darn it!

418
00:06:53,286 --> 00:06:54,956
- Gosh.
- I can't believe this.

419
00:06:55,856 --> 00:06:59,915
(Reborn Rich)

420
00:06:59,995 --> 00:07:00,946
(Overcoming the national crisis,
Opening a New Era)

421
00:07:01,026 --> 00:07:04,795
(February 1998)

422
00:07:08,065 --> 00:07:11,235
This year, prices will continue to rise,

423
00:07:11,805 --> 00:07:13,655
and more people will lose their jobs.

424
00:07:14,175 --> 00:07:17,795
Everyone's earnings will decrease,
and more companies will go bankrupt.

425
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:21,445
All of us will have to shed
a lot of sweat and tears...

426
00:07:24,786 --> 00:07:26,856
while going through this difficult time.

427
00:07:29,526 --> 00:07:31,816
He finally became President
after three failed attempts. But for what?

428
00:07:31,896 --> 00:07:34,785
He was handed over a key to an empty shed.

429
00:07:34,865 --> 00:07:37,115
Goodness. How unlucky.

430
00:07:37,195 --> 00:07:38,256
He'll want to be remembered...

431
00:07:38,336 --> 00:07:41,666
as the president who filled the shed
and taught the rich a lesson.

432
00:07:42,406 --> 00:07:44,355
They're calling this a breakfast meeting.

433
00:07:44,435 --> 00:07:46,655
But clearly, they summoned all of us
to discipline us.

434
00:07:46,735 --> 00:07:48,496
At this early hour...

435
00:07:48,576 --> 00:07:51,315
Anyway, do you sleep well these days?

436
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:53,965
You know, Ahjin Motors' situation.

437
00:07:54,045 --> 00:07:55,845
It could happen to us too, you know.

438
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:01,946
Even Ahjin, the second biggest
auto company, has collapsed.

439
00:08:02,026 --> 00:08:04,396
Will Soonyang Motors be all right?

440
00:08:05,925 --> 00:08:09,345
After listening to you,
I am concerned indeed.

441
00:08:09,425 --> 00:08:10,446
(Cheongwadae, The Republic of Korea)

442
00:08:10,526 --> 00:08:13,155
Daeyoung Motors
is the number one auto company.

443
00:08:13,235 --> 00:08:17,026
The company should go global
and bring in dollars, if anything.

444
00:08:17,106 --> 00:08:20,336
But they're busy power-tripping
in this small country.

445
00:08:22,906 --> 00:08:25,416
Going global will be hard, right?

446
00:08:26,846 --> 00:08:28,985
Should Soonyang show you how it's done?

447
00:08:36,985 --> 00:08:39,935
Chairman Jin, you're surely way
more magnanimous than I am.

448
00:08:41,726 --> 00:08:43,265
Your younger son.

449
00:08:45,495 --> 00:08:48,726
He came to me and said he wanted
to take over Hando Steel.

450
00:08:48,806 --> 00:08:50,685
Had he been my son,

451
00:08:50,765 --> 00:08:53,706
I would've taught him a lesson
and disowned him long ago.

452
00:08:54,676 --> 00:08:57,966
That brat dared to stab
his brother in the back.

453
00:08:58,046 --> 00:09:00,275
But you protected him
because he's your son.

454
00:09:03,285 --> 00:09:04,285
It certainly...

455
00:09:05,456 --> 00:09:06,785
changed my opinion of you.

456
00:09:08,956 --> 00:09:11,696
- You...
- Mr. President is here.

457
00:09:19,336 --> 00:09:21,126
What does Cheongwadae think?

458
00:09:21,206 --> 00:09:23,726
They didn't even bring up
the IMF and company succession, right?

459
00:09:23,806 --> 00:09:25,856
Will they reform the conglomerate system?

460
00:09:26,735 --> 00:09:29,046
Do they want us to lose all
our subsidiaries?

461
00:09:29,576 --> 00:09:32,466
Oh, right. I heard we might have to give up
our private assets too.

462
00:09:32,546 --> 00:09:33,816
That won't happen, right?

463
00:09:35,145 --> 00:09:36,945
Did you already agree to everything?

464
00:09:37,556 --> 00:09:39,385
- Father.
- Dong Ki!

465
00:09:41,326 --> 00:09:42,426
You...

466
00:09:55,206 --> 00:09:57,235
Cheongwadae seemed determined.

467
00:09:57,875 --> 00:10:00,455
They plan to restructure
the major corporations,

468
00:10:00,535 --> 00:10:02,285
and Soonyang won't be an exception.

469
00:10:09,245 --> 00:10:12,255
What will Cheongwadae do
about Ahjin Motors?

470
00:10:14,426 --> 00:10:17,545
If they sit on the issue,
the company will rack up more debt.

471
00:10:17,625 --> 00:10:19,246
Then no one would want
to acquire the company.

472
00:10:19,326 --> 00:10:21,886
The domestic automotive industry
is suffering big-time.

473
00:10:21,966 --> 00:10:23,685
Who'd be willing to acquire Ahjin Motors?

474
00:10:23,765 --> 00:10:26,716
Who'd be crazy enough to do that,
unless they were shot in the head?

475
00:10:26,796 --> 00:10:27,806
Me.

476
00:10:30,165 --> 00:10:31,635
Ahjin Motors.

477
00:10:32,706 --> 00:10:34,446
Soonyang will buy the company.

478
00:10:35,405 --> 00:10:38,636
Father, you wish to buy Ahjin
with all that's going on?

479
00:10:38,716 --> 00:10:41,435
If a businessman sits in a safe zone
and doesn't budge,

480
00:10:41,515 --> 00:10:42,636
his butt will rot.

481
00:10:42,716 --> 00:10:46,356
Father, the interest on their loan
is 30 percent.

482
00:10:47,015 --> 00:10:48,506
Ahjin has nothing but debts.

483
00:10:48,586 --> 00:10:50,445
Do you want to volunteer
to take care of the bomb?

484
00:10:50,525 --> 00:10:53,116
At the moment, we should focus
on maintaining Soonyang Motors...

485
00:10:53,196 --> 00:10:55,446
Cheongwadae wishes
to restructure everything.

486
00:10:57,196 --> 00:11:00,346
And as you guys said,
the domestic automotive industry is dead.

487
00:11:03,365 --> 00:11:06,576
Why don't you understand what this means?

488
00:11:07,235 --> 00:11:09,165
Ahjin Motors isn't the bomb.

489
00:11:09,245 --> 00:11:11,065
Soonyang Motors is.

490
00:11:11,145 --> 00:11:14,295
The worst performing automaker
in the country, Soonyang Motors!

491
00:11:19,816 --> 00:11:21,485
Taking over Ahjin Motors?

492
00:11:22,525 --> 00:11:23,826
It's not a choice.

493
00:11:24,596 --> 00:11:25,846
We must do it to survive.

494
00:11:27,765 --> 00:11:28,796
To survive.

495
00:11:30,265 --> 00:11:31,336
Okay?

496
00:11:32,495 --> 00:11:33,596
Do you understand?

497
00:11:37,806 --> 00:11:41,505
(Ahjin Motors, Changes in Shareholders)

498
00:11:47,546 --> 00:11:50,015
Your grandfather, Chairman Jin.

499
00:11:51,015 --> 00:11:54,216
He'll be determined
to acquire Ahjin Motors.

500
00:11:55,086 --> 00:11:58,116
Because it's the only way
to protect Soonyang Motors.

501
00:11:58,196 --> 00:12:00,646
Acquiring Ahjin Motors,
the number two company in the industry,

502
00:12:00,726 --> 00:12:02,445
means their market dominance will go up.

503
00:12:02,525 --> 00:12:04,455
And if they share the production lines,

504
00:12:04,535 --> 00:12:06,785
they can reduce costs too.

505
00:12:06,865 --> 00:12:09,905
Most importantly,
they'd have to grow Soonyang Motors...

506
00:12:11,005 --> 00:12:12,195
to avoid restructuring.

507
00:12:12,275 --> 00:12:13,306
(Soonyang)

508
00:12:17,206 --> 00:12:18,716
That being said...

509
00:12:22,586 --> 00:12:26,186
If I were one of those people
at Cheongwadae,

510
00:12:27,586 --> 00:12:29,486
I'd give Ahjin Motors to Chairman Jin.

511
00:12:30,456 --> 00:12:32,246
Not a new investment firm like us...

512
00:12:32,326 --> 00:12:34,526
with no experience
in management whatsoever.

513
00:12:35,765 --> 00:12:37,085
Are you confident?

514
00:12:37,165 --> 00:12:39,655
Are you sure we won't lose
Ahjin Motors to Soonyang?

515
00:12:39,735 --> 00:12:42,685
I assure you that Soonyang
will never acquire Ahjin Motors.

516
00:12:46,576 --> 00:12:48,976
They'll soon realize that
they've fallen prey...

517
00:12:50,346 --> 00:12:51,676
to the winner's curse.

518
00:12:54,745 --> 00:12:56,546
The internal reserves?

519
00:12:57,785 --> 00:13:00,056
- All of it?
- Yes.

520
00:13:00,716 --> 00:13:02,945
The bidding war over Hando Steel...

521
00:13:03,025 --> 00:13:05,655
was extremely fierce, Father.

522
00:13:06,726 --> 00:13:09,646
With the foreign exchange differences
soaring,

523
00:13:09,726 --> 00:13:11,365
we had unexpected expenses, sir.

524
00:13:15,106 --> 00:13:16,206
What can we do?

525
00:13:17,635 --> 00:13:19,385
Try to take out a loan from a bank.

526
00:13:20,706 --> 00:13:23,565
We've maxed out our limits
at all the major banks,

527
00:13:23,645 --> 00:13:25,895
so we can't take out an additional loan, sir.

528
00:13:30,686 --> 00:13:32,486
Is that also because of Hando Steel?

529
00:13:33,985 --> 00:13:35,025
Yes, sir.

530
00:13:42,265 --> 00:13:43,615
Our real estate properties.

531
00:13:44,796 --> 00:13:46,066
Let's sell them.

532
00:13:47,265 --> 00:13:48,265
The thing is,

533
00:13:49,436 --> 00:13:51,236
we already used the valuable ones...

534
00:13:51,806 --> 00:13:53,706
- as collateral to take out...
- So?

535
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:57,816
Are you saying we can't afford
to acquire Ahjin Motors?

536
00:13:59,716 --> 00:14:00,946
I'm sorry, Father.

537
00:14:06,216 --> 00:14:09,376
We wouldn't have had any problems
without the financial crisis.

538
00:14:09,456 --> 00:14:11,945
If only Dong Ki hadn't egged
on the chairman of Daeyoung...

539
00:14:12,025 --> 00:14:14,246
to increase the bid for Hando Steel...

540
00:14:14,326 --> 00:14:16,216
Father, I was just...

541
00:14:16,296 --> 00:14:17,495
Enough, both of you!

542
00:14:22,365 --> 00:14:25,005
It's all my fault.

543
00:14:26,336 --> 00:14:27,405
Father.

544
00:14:30,846 --> 00:14:31,946
Hang Jae.

545
00:14:38,255 --> 00:14:39,316
Yes, sir.

546
00:14:40,985 --> 00:14:42,086
You are...

547
00:14:44,525 --> 00:14:46,326
my son.

548
00:14:53,495 --> 00:14:55,265
(Arrivals Exit)

549
00:15:14,985 --> 00:15:16,155
Mr. Jin Seong Jun?

550
00:15:20,655 --> 00:15:22,705
You're waiting for your secretary, right?

551
00:15:24,466 --> 00:15:25,995
They'll be a bit late.

552
00:15:27,566 --> 00:15:30,566
Yes, sorry! Oh, boy.

553
00:15:31,535 --> 00:15:33,795
Sorry. We apologize.

554
00:15:33,875 --> 00:15:35,446
- We're sorry.
- My gosh.

555
00:15:36,106 --> 00:15:37,496
You guys.

556
00:15:37,576 --> 00:15:40,535
- You can't block the road!
- We're sorry.

557
00:15:40,615 --> 00:15:42,606
- Sorry, we'll hurry.
- I'm very busy right now!

558
00:15:42,686 --> 00:15:45,456
They're getting stalled.

559
00:15:47,885 --> 00:15:50,506
Our suitcases got switched at the airport,

560
00:15:50,586 --> 00:15:52,516
so we meet by fate...

561
00:15:52,596 --> 00:15:55,486
and leave a deep impression on each other.
That's the story.

562
00:15:55,566 --> 00:15:57,696
Before our families set us up officially.

563
00:15:58,635 --> 00:16:00,415
- "We?"
- Jin Seong Jun,

564
00:16:00,495 --> 00:16:01,825
the Soonyang family's eldest grandson,

565
00:16:01,905 --> 00:16:05,496
and Mo Hyeon Min, the only daughter
of the Hyunsung Daily family.

566
00:16:05,576 --> 00:16:06,576
Us.

567
00:16:07,905 --> 00:16:09,866
Hearing that you'd be turned off
by marriage talks...

368
00:16:09,946 --> 00:16:12,266
between the two families,

369
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:14,266
my family came up with this idea
in a rush...

370
00:16:14,346 --> 00:16:17,435
because they really want
to marry me off to your family.

371
00:16:17,515 --> 00:16:21,015
You're showing me all your cards.
Then this game will be no fun.

372
00:16:23,785 --> 00:16:25,276
In your third year of college, you took...

373
00:16:25,356 --> 00:16:28,726
"Understanding Classic British
and American Literature." C minus.

374
00:16:29,395 --> 00:16:30,745
That was your grade, right?

375
00:16:31,765 --> 00:16:34,285
No wonder you have
poor comprehension skills.

376
00:16:34,365 --> 00:16:37,065
I'm trying to tell you that
we should turn the tables.

377
00:16:43,745 --> 00:16:47,245
You look as though you're thinking,
"Where did this nutjob come from?"

378
00:16:48,816 --> 00:16:50,566
You have good comprehension skills.

379
00:16:51,356 --> 00:16:53,575
Yes, you can see.

380
00:16:53,655 --> 00:16:55,885
Tell the elders in your family.

381
00:16:56,785 --> 00:16:59,815
I love myself too much to bet my future
on you just because...

382
00:16:59,895 --> 00:17:01,685
you're from the Soonyang family.

383
00:17:01,765 --> 00:17:03,646
Why can't you take care of it yourself?

384
00:17:03,726 --> 00:17:06,836
My family isn't really in a position
to turn it down.

385
00:17:16,746 --> 00:17:19,746
You look better in person.
I guess you're not photogenic.

386
00:17:41,836 --> 00:17:44,036
I'm sorry, sir.
Did I keep you waiting long?

387
00:17:45,006 --> 00:17:46,496
You may not believe it,

388
00:17:46,576 --> 00:17:48,565
but some stupid newspaper delivery truck...

389
00:17:48,645 --> 00:17:51,436
Of course, I believe you.
It was Hyunsung Daily, right?

390
00:17:51,516 --> 00:17:53,166
Oh, how did you know?

391
00:17:53,246 --> 00:17:55,215
Let's go. The elders must be waiting.

392
00:17:56,016 --> 00:17:57,046
Yes, sir.

393
00:18:01,986 --> 00:18:04,856
- Grandma.
- Oh, my.

394
00:18:05,526 --> 00:18:08,746
My gosh. You did it, sweetheart.

395
00:18:08,826 --> 00:18:10,566
It must've been so hard.

396
00:18:11,365 --> 00:18:14,926
You lived on hamburgers
while studying in that faraway country.

397
00:18:15,006 --> 00:18:17,125
You've lost weight.

398
00:18:17,205 --> 00:18:19,496
No. I gained 5kg, Grandma.

399
00:18:19,576 --> 00:18:20,956
It's water weight.

400
00:18:21,036 --> 00:18:23,196
You're swollen because
you haven't been eating well.

401
00:18:23,276 --> 00:18:26,135
Jeong Rae, what are you waiting for? He must be hungry.

402
00:18:26,215 --> 00:18:28,436
- Let's feed him first.
- Okay.

403
00:18:28,516 --> 00:18:31,286
- Mother, he should go say hello
to Father first.
- All right.

404
00:18:31,856 --> 00:18:34,746
- He's in his study, right?
- Yes, that's right.

405
00:18:34,826 --> 00:18:36,086
- Go on.
- I'll be right back.

406
00:18:50,566 --> 00:18:52,975
Grandpa. It's me, Seong Jun.

407
00:18:53,675 --> 00:18:54,776
I'm coming in.

408
00:19:01,816 --> 00:19:03,016
You're back!

409
00:19:05,885 --> 00:19:09,986
Oh, my. Yes, welcome back.

410
00:19:11,796 --> 00:19:13,125
Let me take a look at you.

411
00:19:14,895 --> 00:19:16,996
My gosh, look at you.

412
00:19:19,066 --> 00:19:22,055
You've done well finishing up...

413
00:19:22,135 --> 00:19:24,875
the studies you always dreaded doing.

414
00:19:25,975 --> 00:19:27,076
My eldest grandson.

415
00:19:28,006 --> 00:19:29,996
My true studies begin now.

416
00:19:30,076 --> 00:19:33,176
I'll stand right by your side
to learn everything I must know.

417
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:36,906
Good. Let's wait and see...

418
00:19:36,986 --> 00:19:39,986
how you earn your keep, my eldest grandson.

419
00:19:41,455 --> 00:19:43,045
Good.

420
00:19:43,125 --> 00:19:46,176
Go get some rest.
You must be tired from traveling.

421
00:19:46,256 --> 00:19:47,296
Okay.

422
00:19:50,496 --> 00:19:51,695
Seong Jun, you are...

423
00:19:52,796 --> 00:19:54,195
the pillar of our family.

424
00:19:57,205 --> 00:20:00,405
So you can get married
with the same attitude.

425
00:20:01,475 --> 00:20:02,506
Do you understand?

426
00:20:03,675 --> 00:20:06,375
You must have found
a suitable candidate, Grandfather.

427
00:20:09,445 --> 00:20:11,486
Okay. Go on now.

428
00:20:20,596 --> 00:20:23,746
She doesn't look like the type
who would cherish her husband.

429
00:20:23,826 --> 00:20:27,055
And especially not the type
who'd be dedicated to her in-laws.

430
00:20:27,135 --> 00:20:30,385
While I was gone, you've mastered
the art of discerning characters.

431
00:20:30,465 --> 00:20:32,135
Goodness. Hey.

432
00:20:32,705 --> 00:20:34,696
If your father hadn't fallen out
of your grandfather's favor,

433
00:20:34,776 --> 00:20:36,826
I wouldn't let you go into this marriage.

434
00:20:39,516 --> 00:20:42,885
Do I have to end up humoring
my daughter-in-law too?

435
00:20:43,546 --> 00:20:44,645
Jeez.

436
00:20:45,316 --> 00:20:46,736
Look at this girl.

437
00:20:46,816 --> 00:20:49,645
Nothing about her says that she's easygoing.

438
00:20:49,725 --> 00:20:50,786
Look at this.

439
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,345
I don't have to look at her photo.

440
00:20:53,425 --> 00:20:55,526
Right? Isn't that right?

441
00:20:56,225 --> 00:20:59,486
Do you want to ask Grandfather
for another suitable girl?

442
00:20:59,566 --> 00:21:00,516
- Mother.
- Yes?

443